# Caching & Confirmation System

## Cache Confirmation Rules
- Store confirmation data **immediately** - no delays
- Show confirmation UI **directly in popup** - no separate windows
- Use `currentPendingConfirmation` pattern for single confirmation
- Clear confirmation data after user action

## Cache Management
- Use `chrome.storage.local` for persistence
- Require user confirmation before saving matches
- Provide cache statistics and export functionality
- Check cache first before making API calls

## Cache Confirmation Pattern
```typescript
// Return object with confirmation data for background script to handle
return {
  url: appleMusicUrl,
  needsConfirmation: true,
  confirmationData: {
    youtubeId,
    youtubeTitle: `${artist} - ${songTitle}`,
    appleMusicArtist: song.artistName,
    appleMusicSong: song.trackName,
  },
  isCached: false,
};
```

## Background Script Confirmation Handling
```typescript
// Handle confirmation if needed
if (result.needsConfirmation && result.confirmationData) {
  console.log("🤔 Song needs confirmation, storing data immediately");
  // Store confirmation immediately - no delays needed
  this.currentPendingConfirmation = result.confirmationData;
  console.log("🤔 Stored pending confirmation:", this.currentPendingConfirmation);
}
```

## Popup Confirmation UI
- Display pending confirmation directly in popup
- Show YouTube vs Apple Music comparison
- Provide "Yes, Correct" / "No, Wrong" buttons
- Update cache based on user decision